rComments: It seemed like his first time teaching this course, so he seemed a little unfamiliar with the course progression. Mostly taught out of the book, so reading the book was more valuable than the lectures. Curved well. Could have spent some more time focusing on underlying theories + principles. Labs frequently didn't work.
